{\rtf1\ansi\deff0\fs20 \par\par{\b SECTION 1: User Authentication Flow}\par
{\b Overview:} Users authenticate via email + password, with optional two-factor verification using TOTP codes.\par
{\b REQ-A1:} The login screen shall accept an email address (RFC 5322 compliant) and a password (min 8 chars).\par
{\b REQ-A2:} On three failed login attempts within five minutes, the account shall be locked for fifteen minutes.\par
{\b REQ-A3:} Users with 2FA enabled shall be prompted for a six-digit TOTP code after password validation.\par
{\b REQ-A4:} Forgotten password flow shall send a reset link valid for one hour to the registered email.\par
{\b REQ-A5:} Session tokens shall expire after eight hours of inactivity and require re-authentication.\par\par\par{\b SECTION 2: Search and Filter Behavior}\par
{\b Overview:} Search supports keyword, date-range, category, and sort-order filters with URL-encoded state.\par
{\b REQ-S1:} The search bar shall return results matching keyword in title, description, or tag fields.\par
{\b REQ-S2:} Date filter shall accept ISO 8601 ranges and default to last 30 days when omitted.\par
{\b REQ-S3:} Category filter shall be multi-select with at least seven predefined categories.\par
{\b REQ-S4:} Sort options shall include relevance, date ascending, date descending, and price.\par
{\b REQ-S5:} Search state shall persist across navigation via URL query parameters.\par\par\par{\b SECTION 3: Payment and Checkout}\par
{\b Overview:} Checkout supports credit card, PayPal, and saved payment methods with PCI-compliant storage.\par
{\b REQ-P1:} Credit card numbers shall be validated using the Luhn algorithm before submission.\par
{\b REQ-P2:} Saved payment methods shall display only the last four digits and card brand.\par
{\b REQ-P3:} Currency shall default to the user locale and be overridable via account settings.\par
{\b REQ-P4:} Promo codes shall be applied at the cart level and reflected before final confirmation.\par
{\b REQ-P5:} Failed payment retries shall preserve the cart state for a minimum of 24 hours.\par\par\par{\b SECTION 4: Notifications and Email Templates}\par
{\b Overview:} The platform sends transactional emails for signup, password reset, order confirmation, and shipping updates.\par
{\b REQ-N1:} Welcome emails shall be sent within 30 seconds of successful signup confirmation.\par
{\b REQ-N2:} Order confirmation emails shall include order ID, items, total, and tracking link placeholder.\par
{\b REQ-N3:} Shipping update emails shall fire on each carrier status change (shipped/in-transit/delivered).\par
{\b REQ-N4:} Users shall be able to unsubscribe from marketing emails via a one-click link.\par
{\b REQ-N5:} All emails shall be rendered in both HTML and plain-text formats for accessibility.\par\par\par{\b SECTION 5: Accessibility and Internationalization}\par
{\b Overview:} The product targets WCAG 2.1 AA compliance and supports nine locales at launch.\par
{\b REQ-I1:} All interactive elements shall have a visible focus indicator with contrast ratio >= 3:1.\par
{\b REQ-I2:} Form fields shall have associated labels readable by screen readers (aria-label or label-for).\par
{\b REQ-I3:} The UI shall support keyboard-only navigation across all primary user flows.\par
{\b REQ-I4:} Language switcher shall persist locale preference per-user and reflect in date/number formatting.\par
{\b REQ-I5:} Right-to-left languages (Arabic, Hebrew) shall mirror the layout via CSS logical properties.\par\par\par{\b SECTION 6: User Authentication Flow}\par
